{"word":"G5442 - φυλάσσω - phylássō - foo-las'-so - Beward","slug":"G5442","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">φυλάσσω</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>phylássō"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>foo-las'-so"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Beward"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x03C6;&#x03C5;&#x03BB;&#x03B1;&#x0301;&#x03C3;&#x03C3;&#x03C9; - phulasso&#x0304;</b> - <i>foo-las'-so</i><p/>Probably from <a href=\"#/G5443\">G5443</a> through the idea of <i>isolation</i>; to <i>watch</i>, that is, <i>be on guard</i> (literally or figuratively); by implication to <i>preserve</i>. <i>obey</i>, <i>avoid:</i> - beware, keep (self), observe, save. Compare <a href=\"#/G5083\">G5083</a>."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/G5438\">G5438</a>, <a href=\"#/G5439\">G5439</a>, <a href=\"#/G5441\">G5441</a>"}]}